      "text": "The author argues that (1) neither Dripps nor West offers convincing critiques of consent-based theories; (2) the alternatives offer presuppose the vitality of consent-based approach to understanding rape; and (3) that both Dripps and West consistently conflate more general moral and political issues with that of the nature of rape.",
      "label": "claim"
