      "text": "Dripps offers a theory of rape built around ideas of sexual property.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU3": {
      "text": "In essence, rape consists of sexual use of another's body where access to the sexual service is the result of illegitimate pressures.",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "ADU4": {
      "text": "Reform of rape law to focus on consent is equally defective; according to This is because 'consent obscures \"the normative issues.\"",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU5": {
      "text": "Robin West, too; rejects understanding rape in terms of consent to sex.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU6": {
      "text": "West offers two critiques of the commodity approach.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU7": {
      "text": "First; the commodity approach is bereft of experiential content: The is not that no one experiences expropriation, but that understanding expropriation does not entail consideration of experience.",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "ADU8": {
      "text": "Second, sex is not properly understood as a commodity at all.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU9": {
      "text": "Consent theory is to be rejected, in part, because conditions are such that no woman can give effective valid consent.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU10": {
      "text": "A consent-based theory of rape need not be vulnerable to the critiques of either Dripps or West.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU11": {
      "text": "Further; a consent-based theory is, in several respects; superior.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU12": {
      "text": "Dripps himself employs the language of autonomy and free exchange.",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "ADU13": {
      "text": "No doubt, the language of consent has been used in ways that are intellectually unacceptable, bizarre, and inconsistent.",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "ADU14": {
      "text": "It is, or should perfectly obvious that words of assent uttered following physical attacks or threats do not normally constitute valid, effective consent.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU15": {
      "text": "The expression of autonomy through control leads directly to considerations of consent.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU16": {
      "text": "Consent enters as the form in which autonomy or agency is expressed or exercised.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU17": {
      "text": "Consent expresses the agreement of the parties to the transfer; creating voluntary exchange of values.",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "ADU18": {
      "text": "None of this matters as to whether this is a case of rape. It is. And it is because there is no consent.",
      "label": "claim"
